Frequently Asked Questions

How often do tubes/glue-boards need changing?

Typically every 6–12 months for tubes; monthly or as required for glue-boards in high-pressure sites.

Where should units be installed?

Install units at 1.8–2.2 m height, away from competing light sources and not above food prep surfaces; ensure they are visible to insect flight paths.

What area does each model cover?

Coverage depends on layout and fly pressure; we'll size the unit after a quick site chat.

Do they produce odour or smoke?

No. Units are odourless and produce no poisonous vapours.

What is the power consumption?

Efficient UV-A tubes draw 15–20W per tube depending on model.

What is the warranty & service?

We provide a 1-year hardware warranty and offer scheduled servicing and fast parts support through United Pest.
